Others: The Houston Rockets won against the Memphis Grizzlies with a score of 128-108.
Jalen Green led the Rockets with 22 points.
Alperen Sengun and Jabari Smith Jr. dominated the rebounding with 15 and 16 rebounds respectively.
The Rockets grabbed 64 rebounds, 23 of them being offensive boards, while the Grizzlies grabbed 43 total rebounds.
The Rockets will be on the road in their next game against the San Antonio Spurs on Oct. 28.
